FT  06 OCT 94 / Fears over code on newspaper delivery
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The National Federation of Retail Newsagents yesterday said the government's
code of practice on national newspaper distribution, published yesterday,
could accelerate the expansion of multiple retailers at the expense of
smaller independents.
Mr David Daniel, director of federation services, said the code, which
requires new newsagents to pay a deposit to secure wholesale supplies,
risked intensifying competition for existing independents and deterring new
ones. It was previously left to wholesalers to decide whether to supply new
newsagents.
