In the first six months of this year, Britain's exports to China grew by
17.3 per cent to Pounds 420.2m compared with the corresponding period
last year, while imports rose by 37.9 per cent to Pounds 781.9m. Among
European Union countries, Britain ranks fourth in exports to China
behind Germany, France and Italy, but in investment terms, Britain leads
the way with Dollars 3bn (Pounds 1.9bn) between 1979-1983, more than
double that of Germany.
