32.3m (USDollars 24.1m), or 55 cents a share, down 12 per cent from CDollars
36.8m, or 62 cents, a year earlier.
Sales were CDollars 754m against CDollars 772m.
Molson Breweries' sales improved with strong exports to the US but profits
were only slightly higher because of Canadian beer price wars.
Mr Marshall Cohen, president, said earlier this year that Molson would seek
further international brewing expansion.
