<HEADLINE>
FT  05 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Midlands Electric buys back 10% of its
shares
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID LASCELLES, Resources Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Midlands Electricity bought back 10 per cent of its shares for Pounds 153.5m
yesterday, following the well-established practice among electricity
utilities.
The buy-back, carried out by Cazenove, the company's stockbrokers, was
undertaken to increase earnings per share, Midlands said. Shareholder
approval was obtained at the annual meeting in August.
The buy-back of 21m shares was made at an average price of 725p. The shares
closed up 13p at 714p as other electricity stocks also gained strongly.
As with a recent buy-back by Northern Electric, the deal was structured in a
way that should enable institutional investors to treat the proceeds as a
distribution qualifying for a tax credit. But Midlands said it was up to
individual investors to negotiate the credits with the Inland Revenue.
</TEXT>
