<HEADLINE>
FT  05 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Protean acquisition
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Protean, the laboratory equipment and water purification specialist, is to
acquire Jenway, the bench-top monitoring and analysis equipment
manufacturer, for Pounds 4.15m.
Funding will be met with Pounds 2.8m in cash, Pounds 1.2m in loan notes and
Pounds 150,000 in Protean ordinary shares.
Essex-based Jenway was established in 1973. For the year to July 31, pre-tax
profits were Pounds 167,000 after non-recurring expenses, on turnover of
Pounds 4.25m.
</TEXT>
