FT  05 OCT 94 / Observer: Red not dead
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
As and when the British Post Office is privatised, will the red pillar box
be destined for the scrap heap? Doomsters fear the familiar piece of street
corner furniture may go the way of telephone booths, which, following the
sale of British Telecom, metamorphosed from sturdy red edifices to
distinctly flimsier glass arrangements.
They should take heart, though, from Bill Cockburn, the Post Office's chief
executive, who claims there are no such terrible schemes afoot. To prove the
point, he keeps a model of the Victorian post box in his office - a
veritable beacon to his commitment to keep them red for e'er and a day.
