<HEADLINE>
FT  05 OCT 94 / Observer: Rocking the boat
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
If you come from the Rock of Gibraltar you learn how to take life's knocks.
Take Joe Bossano, chief minister of Gibraltar, who has been doing the rounds
 -or at least trying to - at the IMF/World Bank meetings in Madrid this
week.
Bossano, who is about as welcome to the Spanish government as a banderilla
is to a bull, hitched himself up at the last minute to the British
delegation. As a Crown colony, Gibraltar is one of the very few remaining
blobs of pink on the global map so he can't be refused. However, Her
Majesty's man in Madrid knows how to put people down and Bossano was not
invited to Monday night's bash in honour of Kenneth Clarke, Britain's
chancellor of the exchequer. Yesterday Spain's prime minister Felipe
Gonzalez snubbed Bossano again by refusing him an invite to the champagne
and tapas junket marking the formal opening.
Much more of this and Bossano will be declaring independence.
