<HEADLINE>
FT  05 OCT 94 / The Labour Party in Blackpool: Party support group formed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Labour's affiliated unions have formed a new organisation to provide
financial and organisational support to the party. The Trade Union Labour
Party Liaison Committee will be based in the party's head office with a
separate fund, initially of about Pounds 400,000.
The committee will be run by a steering group of the leaders of eight unions
alongside party leader Mr Tony Blair, deputy leader Mr John Prescott, the
party general secretary and party treasurer.
