FT  05 OCT 94 / Pounds 100m for new towns sought
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN AUTHERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr David Curry, the environment minister, yesterday unveiled a programme
aimed at attracting Pounds 100m in private-sector funds for property
development in new towns.
The 'Invest In Success' scheme provides land in new towns at discounted
prices to partnerships between district councils and the private sector. All
are required to use the land for leisure or cultural facilities,
environmental improvements, social uses or low cost housing.
Funding will now go to 15 projects which have been chosen from 34 initial
applicants.
The winning projects are in Peterborough, Welwyn Hatfield in Hertfordshire,
Sunderland, South Ribble and Chorley in Lancashire, Warrington and Runcorn
in Cheshire, Redditch and Telford.
