FT  05 OCT 94 / Cabinet reshuffle for Seoul
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN BURTON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SEOUL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Hong Jae-hyong, South Korean finance minister, was promoted yesterday to
deputy prime minister for economic planning in a reshuffle of the country's
economic ministries.
He succeeds Mr Chung Jai-suk, who resigned due to ill health 10 months after
he was named to the post.
Mr Park Jae-yoon, senior presidential economic adviser, was appointed the
new finance minister, while Mr Han Lee-hun, the vice-economic planning
minister, will replace Mr Park. The three senior officials have been among
the main architects of proposals to deregulate South Korea's economy and
promote financial liberalisation.
'The scope of the cabinet reshuffle has been minimised with a view to
maintaining the current economic policy,' a presidential spokesman said.
Analysts expect little change in economic strategy, though the new team may
try to speed planned reforms. Mr Hong has held various economic posts since
1963.
